					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>199 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>320</height>
										<width>225</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>190</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>199 folios (+3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="22" writtenLines="22">
									<p>The beginning of each new section is written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Many marginal notes.</p>
									<p>Some passages are marked off, several of them in red ink.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi (North African?) semi-cursive script, of 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yoḥanan ben Ya῾ḳov Siraḳusi ha-Gershoni</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 199r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p/>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>There are many Latin notes in the margins, bearing on Christology.</p>
							<p>Folio <locus n="1r"/>: <q>Expositio Midras in XII. Prophetas. Liber rarissimus.</q>
							</p>
							<p>Folio <locus n="199r"/> has a Latin translation of the Hebrew colophon: <q>F. Aurelius Rochensis scripsit dictante Dno Marcello Theologo, die II. (?) Julii 1574.</q>
							</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Egidio da Viterbo</name>, aka Giles of Viterbo (b. 1472, d. 1532), Augustinian friar, bishop and cardinal, a reforming theologian, orator, humanist and poet: inscribed in the colophon as יידיאו, folio 199r.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Midrash. Minor Prophets. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harley 5704.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
